name: FA Cup
summary: The FA Cup, England's oldest football competition, has been embroiled in controversy over the scrapping of replays. This decision has sparked outrage, with Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola slamming it as "unacceptable." The move to eliminate replays was made to ease fixture congestion, but critics argue it undermines the integrity of the competition. Meanwhile, the final will have an Australian presence, with Tottenham featuring Australia's Charli Grant, while the EFL has issued a statement on the changes. Controversy continues to swirl around the decision, with fans questioning the motives of Wrexham owners Rob McElhenney and Ryan Reynolds for supporting the changes. The semi-final between Manchester City and Chelsea was a thrilling encounter, with City ultimately prevailing 1-0 thanks to a late goal from Bernardo Silva. The debate over FA Cup replays is set to continue as the football community awaits the next steps.
